just_use corpus_report.py

# label: WORKHORSE
# role: live regenerable corpus solutions report

Runs `bfs_solver.solve` against every puzzle in
`corpus/sessions.txt` and writes a Markdown file with the
initial board (sorted by first-card value, fenced) plus the
BFS plan per puzzle. Default output:
`~/showell_repos/claude-steve/random020.md` (overwritten
each run).

```
python3 corpus_report.py [--out PATH]
```

Wall: ~3-5s for 21 puzzles. Steve regenerates after any
solver-touching change to verify depths and skim plans.

## Pointers

- Snapshots: `corpus/baseline_pre_engulf.txt`,
  `corpus/baseline_post_engulf.txt`, frozen historical
  `baseline_bfs.txt`, beginner-comparison `baseline.txt`.
- Sibling: `corpus_lab_catalog.py` ports the same corpus
  into the BOARD_LAB gallery (`puzzles.json`).
